<title>SOUTH AFRICA: African Life half year shr, div rise.</title>
<headline>African Life half year shr, div rise.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1996-11-11</dateline>
<text>
<p>Half yr ended September 30</p>
<p>		(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr (cts)		 21.0     vs 16.8</p>
<p>    Div (cts)		 14.0     vs 11.2</p>
<p>    Net surplus	     20.4     vs 12.9</p>
<p>    Gross premium income  231.0    vs 318.1</p>
<p>    Investment income     43.0     vs 28.1</p>
<p>    Single premium income 45.7     vs 181.3</p>
<p>    Recurring prem income 185.3    vs 136.8</p>
<p>Full name: African Life Assurance Company Ltd</p>
<p>NOTE - The firm said that shareholders on the register by Friday, November 15, may elect to receive capitalisation shares instead of the cash interim dividend.</p>
<p>It added that growth of group overhead expenditure would continue to be held at a rate well below that of growth in recurring premium income and this would provide sustained profitability from group operations.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
</text>
